{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> σῐωπ-ή</b>, <br /> rarely <b>σωπή</b> (which see), ἡ, <b>silence</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Tyrannus” 1075, “fragment” 928, 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hippolytus” 911; σ. ὑπεσημάνθη 5th c.BC: Thucydides Historicus 6.32 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; σ. ποιεῖν, ποιεῖσθαι, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Historia Graeca (Hellenica)” 6.3.10, 5th-6th c.BC: Isocrates Orator 12.234 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἦν σ. there was <b>a hush</b> or <b>calm</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Coloneus” 1623, 4th c.BC: Aeschines Orator 2.35: _plural_, τῶν ἀπειράτων ἄγνωστοι σ\">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]. inglorious <b>silence</b> is their lot who make no venture, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “I.” 4(3).30 (48). \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> <b>the habit of silence</b>, ἐκ τῆς σ. τὴν τῆς σωφροσύνης δόξαν θηρᾶσθαι [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 61.21, compare 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus 2.39b, etc. \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> <i>dative</i> σιωπῇ as <i>adverb</i>, <b>in silence</b>, the only case used by [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Homerus Epicus, ἀκὴν ἐγένοντο σιωπῇ 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 3.95, etc.; σ. ἧσο 4.412 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; ἐπ᾽ ὀφρύσι νεῦσε σ. made a sign <b>without speaking</b>,[<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 9.620; σ. πίνειν 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 1.339; σ. πάσχειν ἄλγεα 13.309, compare 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “P.” 4.57 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; στῆναι, πορεύεσθαι, καθῆσθαι σ., [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Hercules Furens” 930, 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 5.3.43, 4th c.BC: Demosthenes Orator 48.31 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; <b>secretly</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 14.310; σιωπῇ τοῦτ᾽ ἀκύρωτον μένει 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Ion” 801, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Equites” 1212. \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G9090","accentedUnicode":"σιωπή","shortDef":"silence","mediumDef":"silence","stepGloss":"silence","stepTransliteration":"siōpē","count":0,"_step_Type":"word"}]}